# HCDE 530 Week 4 — project rules (530 Week4 Project)

## Scope
- Prefer editing only files in this folder unless the task clearly needs the parent repo.
- Python 3; match style and patterns in existing scripts here (stdlib `urllib` vs `requests` as already used per file).

## APIs and secrets
- Never hardcode API keys. Use `.env` and document variable names in `context.md` or the relevant script’s docstring.
- Do not suggest committing `.env` or pasting real keys into rules or chat logs.

## Scripts
- `sports_scores.py` uses `requests` and writes `sports_scores_results.csv` — preserve UTF-8 and CSV column names when changing output.
- `fetch_reviews.py` and `seattle_weather.py` are stdlib-oriented; avoid adding dependencies unless the user asks.

## Changes
- Keep diffs small and task-focused. No drive-by refactors of unrelated course files.
- If adding new dependencies, update `requirements.txt` and mention it in `week4.md` or `context.md` briefly.
